title>2.3.5 Released</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/2-3-5-released/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/2-3-5-released/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 13 Jan 2016 17:58:58 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Release Notes]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=321396</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>Release Notes for 2.3.5 For All users: &#8211; Import ICS compatibility with WordPress 4.4 &#8211; Event location details corrected where Google maps pin marked the wrong location &#8211; When an event with ticket is exported via an ICS feed, the description will include the &#8220;Buy ticket URL&#8221; to help event seekers purchase a ticket for<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-3-5-released/\" title=\"Read2.3.5 Released\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-3-5-released/\">2.3.5 Released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-3-5-released/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Beta testers wanted for our new ticketing feature</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Mon, 28 Sep 2015 21:53:53 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=320846</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>UPDATE: Timely ticketing is now available to all users! Do you have relatively simple ticketing/registration needs? Do you have better things to do than double event entry? Would you rather save money on your ticketing transactions? We&#8217;re looking for 25 beta testers who want to kick around an integrated ticketing solutions for Timely calendar users.  Rather<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/\" title=\"ReadBeta testers wanted for our new ticketing feature\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/\">Beta testers wanted for our new ticketing feature</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Top 10 How-to Videos for your Timely calendar</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Thu, 06 Aug 2015 02:56:30 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Additional Features]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Basic Features]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Featured Events]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Getting Started]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Pre Sale Questions]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Tips and Tricks]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Troubleshooting]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Tutorials]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[video]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[youtube]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=317457</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>Want the most from your Timely calendar? Check out our new Timely Tube YouTube Channel. Our current playlists include a How-to Video Series for WordPress plugin users, Hubs, and a playlist of videos by Timely Users. Check it out at https://www.youtube.com/user/TimelyTube/playlists. These videos will walk you through how to install/embed and use all your Timely tools. They&#8217;ll teach you how to make your Timely calendar<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/\" title=\"ReadTop 10 How-to Videos for your Timely calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/\">Top 10 How-to Videos for your Timely calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>2.2 Beta Now Available</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jan 2015 22:26:43 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=236046</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>Get the Beta now This is a beta release. It could very well break your site. Do not use it on your live site. The beta for our next release, 2.2, is now available. It contains some great new features and a massive pile of bug fixes. Let&#8217;s have a look at some of the<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/\" title=\"Read2.2 Beta Now Available\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/\">2.2 Beta Now Available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-2-beta-now-available/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Free Hosted Calendars Temporarily Unavailable</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2014 02:01:04 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=212996</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>For the next 24hrs we will not be able to provide free Hosted Calendars. Pro and Hub calendars are not affected, you are welcome to purchase those. Also, if you already have a calendar you will not experience any issues. We hope to have this resolved ASAP, watch here for updates.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/\">Free Hosted Calendars Temporarily Unavailable</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/free-hosted-calendars-temporarily-unavailable/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Malware Reported on aggregator.time.ly</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Mon, 15 Dec 2014 18:12:50 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=211868</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>If you are experiencing issues with the buy tickets button resulting in a 404 or a malware warning from Google, please update to the latest version of the calendar. Some months ago we began tracking clicks on the Buy tickets button as we were interested in building a ticketing add-on. The data we collected was<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/\" title=\"ReadMalware Reported on aggregator.time.ly\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/\">Malware Reported on aggregator.time.ly</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/malware-reported-aggregator-time-ly/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>2.1.9 Updated Beta</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2014 21:04:25 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=204342</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>We have made some changes to the earlier beta, and a new release is available now. Thanks for sending in your bug reports! Here are the full release notes for this release. Features/Improvements Improved calendar feeds import from Google calendar Made calendar behaviour across browsers more consistent &#8211; fixed issue where some of the elements<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/\" title=\"Read2.1.9 Updated Beta\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/\">2.1.9 Updated Beta</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-9-updated-beta/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>2.1.9 Beta Available</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2014 12:07:06 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=202570</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>We have been hard at work over the last two weeks and we now have 2.1.9 just about ready to go. You can download it now and let us know what you think. It contains numerous bug fixes. Removed unwanted URLs from print view Fixed multi day events display in Month view Improved legacy theme<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/\" title=\"Read2.1.9 Beta Available\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/\">2.1.9 Beta Available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-9-beta-available/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Add beautiful (and legal) images to your events</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Thu, 27 Nov 2014 20:33:21 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rik Logtenberg]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Tips and Tricks]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=200099</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>Photos and images are the most engaging type of content on the Internet. Photos are a whopping 10x more likely to be shared. The more photos you have on your calendar, the more you will engage your audience. The best way to add images to your events is to get the original event poster as<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/\" title=\"ReadAdd beautiful (and legal) images to your events\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/\">Add beautiful (and legal) images to your events</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/add-beautiful-legal-images-events/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>2.1.7 Is Now Available</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Fri, 21 Nov 2014 00:52:51 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=190825</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>2.1.7 was released today. It contains numerous bug fixes and some great new features and improvements. The most exciting is a new setting that forces Posterboard tiles to align in a grid. The setting is found in the Events &#62; Settings &#62; Add-ons &#62; Extended Views menu. Timely is all about making sure you can<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/\" title=\"Read2.1.7 Is Now Available\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/\">2.1.7 Is Now Available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-7-now-available/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Black Monday Sale</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Tue, 18 Nov 2014 23:36:09 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=188646</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>The leaves are turning, the sun is setting early and the rain has set in here in our Vancouver HQ. With our WordPress products now all on sale, what better time to sit down with your site and upgrade your calendar? For a limited time we are offering all of our add-ons for half price!<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/\" title=\"ReadBlack Monday Sale\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/\">Black Monday Sale</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/black-monday-sale/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Facebook Add-on Temporarily Unavailable</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 20 Aug 2014 19:40:30 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=145256</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>In a series a updates made over the past several months Facebook has gradually closed and limited access points Timely users relied on to easily share their events. Gone is the ability to export events from Timely to Facebook and Importing events from pages you have liked or your friends has become increasingly difficult. Now<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/\" title=\"ReadFacebook Add-on Temporarily Unavailable\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/\">Facebook Add-on Temporarily Unavailable</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/facebook-add-temporarily-unavailable/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>2.1 Release</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/2-1-release/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/2-1-release/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Wed, 30 Jul 2014 23:32:21 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\t\t<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=130298</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>It&#8217;s coming! 2.1 was planned for this week, but we decided to take one more week for a bit more testing. We implemented some changes to CSS caching relatively late, and we want to make sure it&#8217;s working very smoothly. We decided it would be worth delaying to get these changes into this release. They make<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-release/\" title=\"Read2.1 Release\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/2-1-release/\">2.1 Release</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/2-1-release/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t\t<item>\n\t\t<title>Architecting for Performance Part 2.</title>\n\t\t<link>http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/</link>\n\t\t<comments>http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/#comments</comments>\n\t\t<pubDate>Thu, 24 Jul 2014 21:11:21 +0000</pubDate>\n\t\t<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeffrey Wilcox]]></dc:creator>\n\t\t\t\t<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n\n\t\t<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=127148</guid>\n\t\t<description><![CDATA[<p>Justas, our lead developer, has posted part 2 in his series on how to build performant plugins for WordPress. In the first instalment he focused on tools you can use to set a baseline, and measure the improvements you have made. In part 2 Justas talks about finding architectural patterns behind your code. Using some<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/\" title=\"ReadArchitecting for Performance Part 2.\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/\">Architecting for Performance Part 2.</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://time.ly\">Website Calendar by Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n\t\t<wfw:commentRss>http://time.ly/architecting-performance-part-2/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n\t\t<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n\t\t</item>\n\t</channel>\n</rss>\n\";s:7:\"timeout\";i:10;s:15:\"force_fsockopen\";b:0;s:10:\"force_feed\";b:0;s:5:\"cache\";b:1;s:14:\"cache_duration\";i:3600;s:28:\"autodiscovery_cache_duration\";i:604800;s:14:\"cache_location\";s:7:\"./cache\";s:19:\"cache_name_function\";s:3:\"md5\";s:13:\"order_by_date\";b:1;s:14:\"input_encoding\";b:0;s:13:\"autodiscovery\";i:31;s:8:\"registry\";r:1660;s:17:\"max_checked_feeds\";i:10;s:20:\"all_discovered_feeds\";a:0:{}s:13:\"image_handler\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"multifeed_url\";a:0:{}s:17:\"multifeed_objects\";a:0:{}s:15:\"config_settings\";N;s:10:\"item_limit\";i:0;s:16:\"strip_attributes\";a:14:{i:0;s:7:\"bgsound\";i:1;s:5:\"class\";i:2;s:4:\"expr\";i:3;s:2:\"id\";i:4;s:5:\"style\";i:5;s:7:\"onclick\";i:6;s:7:\"onerror\";i:7;s:8:\"onfinish\";